    {
      "id": "ee9862109af60732c98a6b8619fb9bc3dcdcb87a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-30 15:36:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI just realized that after landing this patch, lfsck test on the following combinations will fail because there is no remove_ost_objects() on servers:\n\n Lustre 2.1.6 client + 2.1.5 server\n Lustre 2.1.6 client + 2.2.0 server\n Lustre 2.1.6 client + 2.3.0 server\n\nFor the current Lustre b2_1 branch, lfsck test passes on the above combinations.\n\nShould we add Lustre version check codes here to determine whether using \"do_rpc_nodes $1 remove_ost_objects $@\" or not?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "3b2b16c2f64258fccb8db11941bc69955486e26f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-30 23:18:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWe will definitely be running 2.1.6->2.1.5 interop testing, and likely 2.1.6->2.3.0 as well, so I'd prefer to keep that working if we know in advance it would break.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "79fed1736472892ffa13bd7596acecc3eff2fb87",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-30 13:17:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nPlease add server version check codes. Thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
